 <h3 class="subheading">Expected Pricing and Market Positioning</h3>
<p>Pricing will be the deciding factor for the BSA Scrambler 650's success, needing to be competitive yet reflective of its premium British heritage and high-quality build.</p>
<p><span class="font-weight-700">Estimated Pricing Strategy</span></p>
<p>Given the pricing of the current Gold Star and the necessary component upgrades (spoked wheels, long-travel suspension, high exhaust), the Scrambler will command a premium.</p>
<ul>
<li><span class="font-weight-700">Expected Price Range (Ex-Showroom, India): </span> The base model is projected to start between <span class="font-weight-700">Rs 3.40 Lakh and Rs 3.60 Lakh.</span></li> 
<li><span class="font-weight-700">Expected Price Range (Top-Spec Pro/Touring Variant): </span> A fully-kitted version (with accessories like bash plate, handguards, and potential connectivity features) could reach <span class="font-weight-700">Rs 3.60 Lakh to Rs 3.80 Lakh.</span> </li>
</ul>
<p>This pricing strategically places it above the current <span class="font-weight-700">Royal Enfield 650 cc </span> twins (which are under 3.5 Lakh) but potentially below the top-end Triumph scramblers, offering a powerful value proposition in the premium segment.</p>
